<title>HONG KONG: BOS unit Countrywide to issue FRCD.</title>
<headline>BOS unit Countrywide to issue FRCD.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-01-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Countrywide Corp Ltd, acting through its Hong Kong branch, plans to issue a US$100 million floating rate certificate of deposit, bankers said.</p>
<p>The issue will be guaranteed by its parent Countrywide Banking Corp.</p>
<p>Overseas Union Bank Singapore is the arranger, they said.</p>
<p>Countrywide Banking Corp is wholly owned by the Bank of Scotland.</p>
<p>No further details were available.</p>
<p>The issuer completed a US$150 million five-year floating rate notes issue last August that was arranged by UBS Hong Kong. The notes pay a coupon of 15 basis points over the three-month London Interbank Offered Rate.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6960</p>
